I simply lucked into my bracer due to the ilis bug in Sebilis.  A 'shroom was the first mob to appear, we killed it and camped.  Jorlain had the presense of mind to loot it just before we all camped out and it had a bracer.  If not for that, I'm sure I'd still be using my guise most of the time.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure making the warrior armor drop more frequently is the real answer.  Since it is argueably better than Indicolite, it should probably be more rare than Indicolite.  I think it's rarity right now is about right, it's all of the other class armor that is way too readily available.  If anything, other class armor should be rare drops off random mobs just like cobalt.  Of course this won't happen, and once again it will take 6 months of camping in the same dungeon to get a helm and bracer (sound like Hate?).<br>
<br>
My guess is that the drop rate will increase shortly after the next EQ expansion.  There will likely be warrior armor better than Cobalt in the new lands so they will need to tweak the drop rate in Sebilis to keep warriors going there, just like they've done with Hate.<br>
<br>
